<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Imgur Gallery</title><link>https://imgur.com</link><description>description</description><lastBuildDate>2022-02-23 23:12:23.336732</lastBuildDate><item><title>13th favorite. Would favorite again.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/oxCX3iR</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/szWJbgk.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Did I upload with sound on? I hope sound is on. Don't wanna be one of those people.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/oxCX3iR</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ExtraAverage]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Story time.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/SYcXgKu</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/l0yuUKg.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This year I put in for my employees to get raises. Everyone has been working really hard and is deserving. Not knowing at all what they get paid (we are an international company and they have a separate HR for that country) raises are approved and I finally have a chance to see what their salaries are. My only female employee in one country basically makes 1/3 of what her male counterparts make. 1/3….</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1LPTrpJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We just recently hired a guy who makes twice as much as her… this is a girl who works very hard and is a model employee, she does everything the guys do and sometimes even better). I end up escalating this to everyone in the company. I make charts and document the whole thing… undeniable evidence. Even sending a note to my boss saying “hey if I get fired this is why” lol. Basically putting the company in a position where they either have to react to this or now there is a paper trail of gender discrimination. HR is supper fast to react and have a recommendation within 12 hours. We’re going to pay her 3x her current salary and bring her up to what she’s deserving of. Having said this I feel really good about my company for doing this… we’ll at least fixing it.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/QUoHU0v.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I’m not here to gloat or feel good, merely to point out an unfairness that exists. And even if this was a coincidence of circumstance, I still feel like women often time get shafted. This occurred in a country where women are often discriminated against and although we obviously see what’s wrong here in the western culture it exists everywhere. Shit on this all you want but I feel good about this.   I’m a middle aged unaffiliated moderate man who oozes your traditional masculine vibes in every way, but I will always stand up for good people and urge everyone to do the same. Everyone and I do mean everyone deserves fair and equal treatment. This is non negotiable.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Xux5Drw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Thanks for reading. Dog tax.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/SYcXgKu</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[JustSomeRandomBloke]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I've abused the favorite button so 10,000 posts later i found this as my 13th, enjoy</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/a7eiXST</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jUKdfiJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The post i found this on had 25,000 upvotes, if this gets at least 69 i'd be nice</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/a7eiXST</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[StormCrowMith]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>My sister died today</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9i1b2fD</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wGRnVaf.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My sister died today. I love her so much and I’m the only friend she really had in life. I feel so heartbroken that she suffered so much in her 33 years on this earth. I can only hope she has peace now and that she knew how much I love her. Her name is Chelsey. Please send her some love.                         -edit- I posted this because she was very alone in the world and I want people to think of her with care, in a way she deserved but rarely got. She had the biggest heart of anyone and suffered so much because of it. Thank you to everyone who said her name or held her in your thoughts, that’s all I can do for her now. She loved kitties and rubber duckies and cooking. If you want to donate in her name, an animal charity, a rehab facility, an organization that fights homelessness, or helps battered women would be good as those all describe her life. She was very silly and had a great sense of humor. She touched the people who she came in contact with. I hope for a few days her spirit lives on through all of you because god damn it life isn’t fair and she deserves better than this.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/9i1b2fD</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[midlifecrisisapproaching]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>This couple is so cute</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/6zxp3sP</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xd3WQL3.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://www.instagram.com/p/CaQV5gFJWlH/?utm_medium=copy_link</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/6zxp3sP</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[thefixer25]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Very true...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/wo5eCIC</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GJUSz72.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></d