Putin can fuck right off to hell.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Q3ODpEJ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ThoughtSandwich]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>13th Favorite</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/OuAd3ah</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Nj1N49l.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>AOC always brings fire</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/OuAd3ah</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[kittykaroshi]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Ukraine, a background</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ZD84E4m</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/icthsx8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I never thought it would be possible, to hear that my people deserved genocides (yes, plural) they endured, but this is not something uncommon to hear from regular Russian when travelling.

Russian and Soviet occupation decimated Ukrainians, Crimean Tatars and other native to our land nationalities, working hard and deliberately for decades to erase our identities. Poets and writers who would use their native tongue instead of language of invaders were often prosecuted. Many of them died in mysterious circumstances, many died in imprisonment.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ekerwir.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Story of Crimean Tatars is especially tragic. After WW2 Russki decided to little more Russkificate Crimea, by getting rid from its indigenous nationality. After brief killings, soviet pigs would put any Tatar they could find on trains and dropped them in the middle of Kazakhstan prairies. Most didn't make it though first winter due to brutal conditions.
This also happened to Ukrainian activists or whole villages, who dared to have an identity.
In Crimea, Tatars were prohibited from owning property. Russians moved into newly vacated homes, and settled them. It is not uncommon for russki to show off rare Tatar art works (often unique styled pottery)  as "family heirlooms"

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deportation_of_the_Crimean_Tatars
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1GjWlYuGg98</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bu6H5gn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>(on the photo, people died from starvation lining streets, because Moscow had to sell all the grain to make moneys)

Holodomor is a series (!) of genocides on Ukrainian people. Russki deliberately would take away all the yield from the fields, leaving Ukrainians to starve to death. Light estimates that quarter of population was deliberately starved to death. Read that sentence twice. Ten of million of people starved to death.
We believe this was to destroy national spirit and way of life. Ukraine before this atrocity was prosperous country with more individualistic outlook. Lots of quite wealthy farmer families, small businesses. This was very unlike in russia where wealth was mostly concentrated into landlord hands and peasants were working fields. Communization didn't go well due to that reasons. In Moscow decision was made to squash this spirit and show wrongness our my people ways by starving most of us to death, following by brutal repression.
On my father's line only his mother survived brutalities of Russians and WW2. His father died in war fighting nazies, grandparents and cousins didn't survive the artificial famine.

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Holodomor
Or watch "Mr Jones" 2019 Movie is about British journalists discovering the atrocity.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ArUXojM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I don't think many of the readers actually made it here. Pretty sure only few ever had to fight for their freedom. I did, most of my friends did. We have ongoing war with Russia, almost every day causing casualties since 2014. Tens of thousands killed, millions displaced.
But we will keep fighting to last drop of blood, hopefully it would be of invading troops.
Fuck Putin and Russia

You can often see the sentiment "Oh, but this is not Russian people, this is their government". Don't buy it. Majority of Russians support current actions. Very few oppose anything, may be corruption of Putins administration. They overwhelmingly hailed occupation of Crimea in 2014. Russians brainwashed by state media, which has even less connection to reality that mr. Trump. Russians are pumped by state crafted stories for generations. This is important thing to understand - there is no journalism in Russia. They have alternate reality in odds with news from any other source than Russian media.

I am filled with anxiety. But I have full resolve to stand for Ukraine. Please, Stand with me.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ZD84E4m</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[svoka]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>(Almost) My 13th</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/W2kKepi</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/udXmD2T.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/W2kKepi</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[amp99]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I scrolled for ages to find this!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/bvovpYX</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/w6Mw9Dt.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>13th favorite, so silly</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bvovpYX</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[LittleChickadee]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Too Many Favorites</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/NqBu0Cl</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VtwX8sj.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I have too many faves, scrolled for a long time and only made it back 3 months. So here is my 13th favorite from my “interesting as fuck” folder.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/NqBu0Cl</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[butterflymkm]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>That's a good point.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/JhbwIzo</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/D9L1DLG.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/JhbwIzo</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tonightat11DOOOOM]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I really miss this man</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/FRqwu5x</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2q6x3Kj.png" style="max-width: 90